pullRequest.body:
Defined inverses for TrivEqExtZero in a way that is consitent with DualNumbers.

Note that $(a + b\epsilon)^{-1} = \frac{1(a - b\epsilon)}{(a + b\epsilon)(a - b\epsilon)} = \frac{a - b\epsilon}{a^2}$
Which becomes $\frac{1}{a} - \frac{b}{a^2}\epsilon$.
We want to be able have left multiplicative inverses $x x^{-1} = 0$
So we write $\frac{b}{a^2} = a^{-1} \cdot b \cdot a^{-1}$

Also included a proof that $x \cdot x^{-1} = 1$ when $\text{fst } x \neq 0$

Could you also prove that `inv_mul_cancel : x‚Åª¬π * x = 1`, in another lemma?

Per [the style guide](https://leanprover-community.github.io/contribute/style.html), this should be:

```suggestion
    (hx : fst x ‚â† 0) : x * x‚Åª¬π = 1 := by
  ext
  ¬∑ rw [fst_mul, fst_inv, fst_one, DivisionRing.mul_inv_cancel (fst x) hx]
  ¬∑ rw [snd_mul, snd_inv, smul_neg, ‚Üê smul_assoc]
    rw [smul_eq_mul, DivisionRing.mul_inv_cancel (fst x) hx]
    rw [one_smul, fst_inv, add_left_neg, snd_one]
```
that is: the line after `by` is *less* indented than the statement.

What you've written gives this lemma the name `TrivSqZeroExt.TrivEqZeroExt.mul_inv_cancel` (note also the typo). I think what you probably want is
```suggestion
protected theorem mul_inv_cancel [DivisionRing R] [AddCommGroup M]
```
where `protected` avoids this getting confused with the global `mul_inv_cancel`.

Also from the style guide:
```suggestion
theorem fst_inv [Neg M] [Inv R] [SMul R·µê·µí·µñ M] [SMul R M]
    (x : tsze R M) : fst x‚Åª¬π = (fst x)‚Åª¬π :=
  rfl
```
I think these are probably good `@[simp]` lemmas

When you have adjacent rewrites like this, we would normally combine them. Here's that version, also with some steps merged together by finding slightly more relevant lemmas:
```suggestions
  ext
  ¬∑ rw [fst_mul, fst_inv, fst_one, mul_inv_cancel hx]
  ¬∑ rw [snd_mul, snd_inv, snd_one, smul_neg, smul_smul, mul_inv_cancel hx, one_smul, fst_inv,
      add_left_neg]
```
Note also that for symmetry this puts both the fist and second goal in `¬∑`.

Can you make a similar change to the proofs below?

I'm afraid you very much took the long way here; this doesn't need `hr` at all:
```suggestion
  ext
  ¬∑ rw [fst_inv, fst_inl, fst_inl]
  ¬∑ rw [snd_inv, fst_inl, snd_inl, snd_inl, smul_zero, smul_zero, neg_zero]
```
This one is a good `simp` lemma too, as `0` is clearly simpler than the LHS!

```suggestion
instance instInv [Neg M] [Inv R] [SMul R·µê·µí·µñ M] [SMul R M] : Inv (tsze R M) :=
```

is the new convention. Only this name needs to change (because it is an instance)
This one should be in the `TrivSqZeroExt` file, stated as `(1 : tsze R M)‚Åª¬π = 1`; and similarly for `0`.

Here's a proof of this:
```suggestion
protected theorem mul_inv_rev [DivisionRing R] [AddCommGroup M]
    [Module R·µê·µí·µñ M] [Module R M] [SMulCommClass R·µê·µí·µñ R M] (a b : tsze R M) :
    (a * b)‚Åª¬π = b‚Åª¬π * a‚Åª¬π := by
  ext
  ¬∑ rw [fst_inv, fst_mul, fst_mul, mul_inv_rev, fst_inv, fst_inv]
  ¬∑ rw [snd_inv, snd_mul, snd_mul, fst_mul, mul_inv_rev, smul_add, op_smul_op_smul]
    simp only [smul_comm, smul_smul, ‚Üê op_mul, smul_add, fst_inv, snd_inv, smul_neg]
    obtain ha0 | ha := eq_or_ne (fst a) 0
    ¬∑ simp [ha0]
    obtain hb0 | hb := eq_or_ne (fst b) 0
    ¬∑ simp [hb0]
    rw [inv_mul_cancel_right‚ÇÄ ha, add_comm, mul_inv_cancel_left‚ÇÄ hb, neg_add]
```
